Altron reports that Tim Jacobs has resigned as acting chief financial officer of the technology group to assume a permanent CFO role at a multinational group, as from 19 October 2018. Andrew Holden, the current chief operating officer (COO) of Altron will assume the joint role of COO and acting CFO on 19 October 2018. Holden has extensive experience in the ICT sector, having been with the Altron group for the past 24 years, the group said. “The board thanks Mr Jacobs for his contribution to the company and wishes him well in his future endeavours,” it said. Read: Altron expects massive jump in earnings